node.text:
This might be my new fav pic of these two. 🥺

Having two male dogs can be hard. Now I get why experienced breeders always recommend getting the opposite sex as the second dog. 

We still manage Geordi and Scotty carefully and always supervise them, but I’m happy to report that they’ve been getting along well and Geordi’s being a patient big brother. 

What has helped us the most is recognizing when Geordi wants personal space from Scotty, and making sure we give that to him before things escalate. It’s been a slow process but worth the effort to see them have fun together!

node.text:
Scotty went to his first lure coursing trial today! We thought he would do really well because he has a lot of natural prey drive – instead, he just happily trotted along and got one of the SLOWEST times of the day. 🐢🤣😅 (swipe to see the video!)

For those who aren’t familiar with this canine sport, the dog chases a mechanized, plastic lure that simulates live prey. It’s one of our favorite events and I recommend trying it out! No previous training necessary. 

Thank you @emwng for the photos! ☺️
